    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus containing several species of fungi that exist as asexual forms (or anamorphs) and are pathogenic (disease-causing) in humans. Aspergillus species are highly aerobic and are found in almost all oxygen-rich environments, where they commonly grow as molds.</Note_Text>
